      "name": "Prediction of accident severity using road traffic accident data",
      "description": "Experiment package for predicting road traffic accident severity from environmental conditions using a supervised Random Forest model. Input data is sourced from the EU open data portal (Leeds City Council road traffic accidents), retrieved exclusively from the TU Wien DBRepo REST API. The pipeline categorizes severity into Minor (0), Serious (1), and Fatal (2). Individual components carry their own licences: input data is under OGL v3.0, code under MIT, and generated outputs under CC BY 4.0.",
